3 C. In addition to civil penalties, the commissioner may assess the
4 proportionate costs of the adjudicatory hearing against the offender. The
5 commissioner shall determine the amount of costs to be assessed.
6 D. The commissioner may institute civil proceedings to enforce his
7 rulings in the district court for the parish in which the violation occurred.
8 E. The commissioner may institute civil proceedings seeking injunctive
9 relief to restrain and prevent the violation of the provisions of this Part, or of
10 the rules and regulations adopted pursuant to the provisions of this Part, in the
11 district court for the parish in which the violation occurred.
12 §4750.4. Rules and regulations
13 The commissioner may adopt rules and regulations necessary to
14 implement this Part. All rules and regulations shall be adopted in accordance
15 with the provisions of the Administrative Procedure Act.
16 §4750.5. Effectiveness
17 The provisions of this Part shall become effective only upon a final ruling
18 by the United States Supreme Court holding that prohibitions on cell cultured
19 food products do not violate the United States Constitution; however, nothing
20 in this Part shall prohibit accredited institutions of higher education in this state
21 from conducting research on cell cultured food products.
